*Need of Spring Security*

Spring Security is needed to protect web applications and APIs from unauthorized access and security threats. Modern applications handle sensitive user data such as passwords, personal information, payments, and private resources, so proper security is essential.

Why Spring Security is Important
Prevents unauthorized users from accessing the application
Provides secure login and authentication mechanisms
Controls user access using roles and permissions
Encrypts and securely stores passwords
Protects applications from attacks like:
CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery)
Session hijacking
Clickjacking
Secures REST APIs and backend services
Manages user sessions securely
Supports modern authentication methods like JWT and OAuth2

Without security, applications become vulnerable to data theft, unauthorized access, and cyberattacks. Spring Security simplifies implementing strong security in Spring Boot applications using built-in features and configurations.